sentences: Gary Anthony Catona (born 25 September 1952) is an American author and voice coach, who describes himself as a "Voice Builder".
He moved to Austin, Texas in 1980 to research the mechanics of voice production and voice anatomy.
In 1982, Catona began to work with clients who had damaged their voices from accident, surgery, injury or illness.
Thinking as Sport and Dance: Learn the Power of Creative Thinking ISBN 978-0595433742 (2008)
Wisdom for Singers and Philosophers ISBN 978-1532042591 (2018)
His clients have also included singers such as Andy Williams, Brian Wilson (The Beach Boys), Dawn Robinson (En Vogue), Babyface, Jesse McCartney, Paula Abdul and Lenny Kravitz.
